            Welcome to my new site
            I am a medical doctor and a Master of Public Health
            candidate specializing in Global Health at the University of
            Washington. I earned my MD in 2021 from the Universidad
            Nacional Mayor de San Marcos in Lima, Peru. Since 2019, I
            have been working with the CRONICAS Center of Excellence in
            Chronic Diseases at the Universidad Peruana Cayetano Heredia
            in Peru. My research focuses on the link between adverse
            experiences during pregnancy, the perinatal period, and
            infancy, and the development of cardiometabolic diseases
            during youth and young adulthood.
            More info about my CV here: CV
